## Economic yield

"Economic yield" means yield as a function of both biophysical and market variables (see Appendix for more details).

* Economic bean yields projected to increase throughout Sub-Saharan Africa out to 2050, although Tanzania and Congo may see yields level off and then decline around 2040.

